{"body": "To be consistent I've changed every `===` by `is_a?` except one class `ActiveSupport::Duration` because `===` i s [redefined there](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/master/activesupport/lib/active_support/duration.rb#L52). By the way - this code looks too ugly. Even speed for `is_a?` and `===` the same I still see points for `is_a?`:\r\n\r\n1. It looks more readable\r\n2. [Ruby style guide](https://github.com/bbatsov/ruby-style-guide) says to avoid `===` and gives explanation why", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/19014388", "created_at": "2013-06-05T22:46:54Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10852#issuecomment-19014388", "updated_at": "2013-06-05T22:46:54Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10852, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/ka8725", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6228fc7c96122d25c088b7dee54db273?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ffbb872814b0007fff47209e46c82c687.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/received_events", "gravatar_id": "6228fc7c96122d25c088b7dee54db273", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "ka8725", "type": "User", "id": 243846, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ka8725/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237db2cbd3543c1510087fc"}, "id": 19014388, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10852"}
